<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/392a68f1cb736c14d89f6dce47522da8.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 5 and b = 3. Calculate:</p>
<p>
c = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
A = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place. Give angles in <em>degrees</em>.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>5.8</li><li>59.0</li><li>31.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={5}^{{2}}+{3}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={25}+{9}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={34}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{34}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{5.8309518948453}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{5.8}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arctan{{\left(\frac{{5}}{{3}}\right)}}}\approx{59.036243467926}\approx{59}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{59.036243467926}^{\circ}\approx{30.963756532074}\approx{31}</m>.</p>

</solution>
